node.text:
Don’t miss the exhibition dedicated to the work of #IrvingPenn in collaboration with #VogueItalia and the Irving Penn Foundation, on display at @CardiGallery in Milano, from today to December 22nd. 

Considered to be one of the greatest photographers of the 20th century, Irving Penn (1917-2009) radically modernized photography as a medium, creating a canon that would manifest a rich and influential legacy of commercial and personal work. Penn joined @VogueMagazine in the early 1940s and he continued to work with the magazine throughout his career. Breaking all convention, Penn approached photography as an artist, opening his own studio and expanding the medium’s creative potential at a time when the photograph was primarily understood as a means of communication.

Click the link in bio if you want to discover more about the exhibition.
Text by Vogue Italia’s Culture Editor @_Federico_Chiara_

node.text:
With the artwall created by illustrator and graphic designer @starrenco in the heart of Milan, @off____white inaugurates a global initiative in the name of female creativity, which will be unfolded through two other events around the world. Costanza's drawing, visible at Colonne di San Lorenzo for the entire month of September, takes inspiration from the unique shapes of the burrow bag, one of the most iconic items by Off-White™. 
Take a look at the video to discover how the project was born.

Credits
Talent Costanza Starrabba wearing @off____white 
Video by @maranif

node.text: "This tattoo got me into a lot of trouble because I had a contract and I wasn't supposed to get tattoos and I did; but it was worth it because I love this tattoo and the meaning behind it". Watch as British supermodel Jourdan Dunn shares the story behind her three most favourite tattoos and reveals what makes them so special.

node.title: @JourdanDunn reveals the empowering message of her tattoos

node.text:
Today we announce the 35 photographers selected for the upcoming #PhotoVogueFestival exhibition through the open call on #PhotoVogue, @Picter_com and Instagram. On Picter alone we received 24.913 images, 2.949 projects by 2.513 photographers from 98 different countries, 6 continents. 
 
Here are the selected artists: @tendercoconut_, @Alessandro.Iovino_, @BettinaPittaluga, @BryanThomasphoto, @delaliayivi, @diiegotv, @di_mathopa, @ElenaHelfrecht, @Elliott.Verdier, @FabioLasin, @Gabriele.Cecconi, @heathatrottlives, @Reanie_Beanie, @l4artiste, @jaircoll, @JodiemBateman, @Juan_Brenner, @Kaiykym, @LauraPannack, @lebo.th, @LeonardPongo, @LisandroSuriel, @Kuca_Magda, @MousLamrabat, @plantationofficial, @elriveriver, @RobertAndyCoombs2, @tondopo, @SaraBennettBrooklyn, @SilvanaTrevale, @SuleikaMueller, @Sushavan_Nandy, @africatotheworldzw, @thembinkosih15, @panremembrance. The artists have been selected by an international jury consisting of experts from across the world, with different backgrounds and vision so as to try to provide the most inclusive and multifaceted perspective. 
 
Photo Vogue Festival has always tried to challenge the danger of single, monolithic stories, and to push a multiplicity of points of view. For its 6th edition, titled “Reframing History”, we wanted to explore the projects that have reclaimed an alternative, different way of telling a tale. 
For the very first time - as part of the Reframing History scouting initiative - PVF launched a grant in collaboration with Studio RM, a prestigious creative studio with offices in London and New York, specialising in colour grading and post production for film, print and digital.
The two participants that will receive a 5,000€ cash grant each, are Lisandro Suriel and River Claure. 
 
Discover more about #VIReframingHistory at the link in bio.

node.text:
Photo Vogue Festival 2021: FREE Digital Portfolio Review! DEADLINE October 15th! Don't miss the chance to have your work reviewed by incredibly talented editors, publishers and curators! 
 
For your chance to be shortlisted, send by October 15th an email to pvf@condenast.it accompanied by your portfolio (a selection of 10/15 images in pdf format), a biography, a contact number and a link to your website. The free digital portfolio review is open to any kind of photographic genre, from art and fashion to photojournalism and documentary. If selected you won't need to be in Milan like for the past editions because the portfolio review is digital. You can apply from anywhere!
 
The review will be on Saturday 13th of November. The best portfolios will be selected by the #VogueItalia team - composed by @AlessiaGlaviano, ChiaraNonino and @Maranif - and the photographers will have the opportunity to have their work freely reviewed by key industry experts - top international photo editors, publishers and curators: @AlessiaGlaviano @AmberTerranova @AstridLepoultier @Azubogu @bptuazon @bertansel @BrunoCeschel @ChiaraNonino @elsmdd @photocaptionist #GiuliaZorzi @gwenleegimlay @goliverio_ @IhiroHayami @irene_opezzo @jaehyun_seok @JamesEstrin #JeanFrançoisLeroy @Kdombsadof @KathyRyan @KiraPollack @LarsLindemann_geo @LekgethoMakola @lynettesaid @MaddalenaScarzella @MaggieSteber @mtSalvati #MelissaHarris @MichaelFamighetti @misslalibsekal @MichaelVanHorne @OlfaFeki @OliviercLaurent @PaulMoakley @oseibonsu_ #RahaabAllana @RenataFerri @roseleen @sagal00 @ShannonGhannam @so.ra.na @sunilgupta7402 @williamcult. Thanks to our wonderful reviewers who are giving us their time for free!
 
Click the link in bio to discover the panel of experts that will review your portfolio during the sixth edition of #PhotoVogueFestival and find out more.

node.text: Sophisticated sensuality and confident, grown-up glamour defines @Supriya_Lele’s Spring-Summer 2022 collection, one which sees the London-based designer evolve the body-celebrating, daringly-draped, twisted and vibrant silhouettes she has become synonymous with since launching her brand in 2016. Discover more about the collection—just unveiled at #LondonFashionWeek— in Stories.

node.text: It’s highly likely that @Erdem Moralioglu’s new house in Bloomsbury is haunted. Ever since he moved into that house during the pandemic, Moralioglu’s work has taken on a more demure and sober character, which is, in fact, a bit ghostly. Somehow, the fusion between that sensibility and the old-world glamour that underpins his oeuvre feels appropriate for now. His 15th-anniversary collection—and first runway show since the pandemic—captured that dichotomy in a purified and clarified ode to his own body of work. Presented in the colonnade of the #BritishMuseum (in Bloomsbury), he envisioned it through the wardrobes of Bloomsbury’s best: #EdithSitwell and #OttolineMorrell, whose spirits he could easily have come across on one of his evening strolls across Bedford Square. “I was really fascinated with these two women—both six foot—who knew each other, and donated to the British Museum,” Moralioglu said backstage, highlighting their independent and formidable approaches to life in the early-and mid-20th century. Click the link in bio to read the review by @BritishVogue’s @AndersChristianMadsen and watch more #VogueBackstage contents in Stories.
